		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Okay, an update and a correction.  First, I miscommunicated<BR>
the loc of the Kaladim coin.  It's in South Kal (first zone) <BR>
in the trough-thingy in front of the warrior guild hall. <BR>
<BR>
Finally completed this last week.  Turns out &quot;aimiable&quot; faction<BR>
works for the Erudite enchanter.  Simply use illusion Erudite and<BR>
benevolence and it should work.  Spell is nice.  Tried it on myself<BR>
and it lowered my MR 32 points at level 47.  Be warned, though, it's<BR>
a megataunt on some mobs.  As bad as or worse than the megataunt you<BR>
get when charm breaks in some cases (though curiously not with guards).<BR>
Fighting Allizewsaur in OOT, he absolutely frenzied on me whenever I<BR>
hit him with Tashania and it took forever for two high 40's tanks<BR>
to taunt him away.  Fighting frogs in Lower Guk liveside castle, <BR>
same thing.  Guards, however, in FP and Ogguk or Grobb, I've tashed <BR>
and not gotten a second look during combat.  Go figure.  <BR>
<BR>

			</font>
	
